199
00:18:36,065 --> 00:18:39,438
- You didn't tell her?
- Just leave it alone, Jacob.

200
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:41,846
Tell me what?

201
00:18:42,846 --> 00:18:46,160
Emmett and Paul
had a misunderstanding,

202
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:47,897
there is nothing
to worry about.

203
00:18:47,897 --> 00:18:49,703
Listen to you.

204
00:18:49,703 --> 00:18:51,771
Did you lie
to get her out of town, too?

205
00:18:51,771 --> 00:18:55,715
You should leave.
Now.

206
00:18:55,715 --> 00:18:57,799
She has a right to know.

207
00:18:58,492 --> 00:19:01,042
She is the one
the red-head wants.

208
00:19:02,326 --> 00:19:04,044
Victoria?

209
00:19:05,028 --> 00:19:10,061
- Alices's vision.
- I was trying to protect you.

210
00:19:10,061 --> 00:19:12,240
By lying to me.

211
00:19:14,757 --> 00:19:17,021
Okey. We're gonna talk
about this, but...

212
00:19:17,630 --> 00:19:18,799
You!

213
00:19:19,362 --> 00:19:21,170
Why haven't you
called me back?

214
00:19:24,282 --> 00:19:26,704
I had nothing to say.

215
00:19:28,506 --> 00:19:31,128
- Well, I have tons. Hold on.
- Hey.

216
00:19:33,016 --> 00:19:34,218
Bella.

217
00:19:34,673 --> 00:19:37,592
- Edward, you have to trust me.
- I do trust you.

218
00:19:38,768 --> 00:19:40,525
It's him I don't trust.

219
00:19:51,725 --> 00:19:54,781
Lose the grin, Jacob.
We're just going for a ride.

220
00:19:54,781 --> 00:19:56,756
Hold on tight.

221
